.Dd $Mdocdate: June 13 2014 $
.Dt GETENTROPY 2
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm getentropy
.Nd get entropy
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <unistd.h>
.Ft ssize_t
.Fn getentropy "char *buf" "size_t buflen"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
returns a buffer of high-quality seed-grade entropy.
.Pp
This is typically used to seed a process-context generator
like
.Xr arc4random 3 .
.Sh ERRORS
.Nm
.Fn setlogin
will succeed unless:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EFAULT
The
.Fa name
parameter points to an
invalid address.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr arc4random 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
function appeared in
.Ox 5.6 .
